n junta possible:\n\nGeneral Torres, Commanding General of the Bolivian Army, will, according to a reliable source, soon attempt to remove the military junta because of its \"do-nothing\" policy and its refusal to hold elections. Torres and General Seleme, Minister of Government and member of the junta, are on friendly terms.\n\nComment: Torres favors the Nationalist Revolutionary Movement and is known to have opposed the military junta's assuming power last May. His appointment was in the nature of bribery to keep him from cooperating with the opposition. General Seleme has also been maneuvering to oust the junta and may believe that his best chances are with Torres", "token_count": 114, "token_end_0based": 113, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "latin america 10 new attempt to oust bolivian junta possible general torres commanding general of the bolivian army will according to a reliable source soon attempt to remove the military junta because of its do-nothing policy and its refusal to hold elections torres and general seleme minister of government and member of the junta are on friendly terms comment torres favors the nationalist revolutionary movement and is known to have opposed the military junta's assuming power last may his appointment was in the nature of bribery to keep him from cooperating with the opposition general seleme has also been maneuvering to oust the junta and may believe that his best chances are with torres", "unred_source_page": 9}
